name: Vulture mounts
description:
Mountains are protectors of our village, and all the villages next to us. This part of desert is a bit colder because of the mountains that surrounds it, therefore you can see a lot of gardens and greens  unlike the other cities in desert.
The vulture mounts are the most famous mountains near Natanz, with peaks higher than 3500 m , they look so tall although they are not that close to us.
In persian, these mounts are called Karkas, which translates to vulture. They say it's been named Karkas because the peak was so high, even vultures wouldn't fly there. 
---
